&quot;Alright then... who's next? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkalaberia.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vaniadelarian>Vania Delarian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><i>~Kalaberia Citizen~</i></span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#8B4513>(8/8/03 12:43 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://image1ex.villagephotos.com/1898960.jpg width=125 height=200></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Intervension of Fate?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>It is then that Vania's back bumps into the other vampire, causing her to whirl around her gun directly pointed at Steven's heart, but as soon as her eyes land on his she lowers the gun and turns back to the oncoming mass of vampires. It is obvious that this time fear has gripped her. As her body is slightly shaking, though this time it is hard to distinguish if it is from pain or from fear. Isabella's voice once again enters Steven's mind, her calm now gone, only a dark brooding anger. [/i]You would turn your back on your own kind, for a lousy woman? A woman who will die of old age anyhow? Humans are but cattle, they must learn their place rebel.This girl won't even live to see another day for she fights for one thing and only one thing, which I have already destroyed. If you will not bring her to me she will only die by her own hands. If it is your wish to save such a pathetic waste of life then bring her to me, I do not wish to kill her. I mean to take her under my wing, she has great possibilities. Surely you could see that. What human remains as calm as she is facing nearly 20 vampires. None, not even a whole army remains as calm as she is. She is a bred killer. Now bring her to me, and I will bless you with my blood.[/i] Isabella is correct in that Vania is strange. No human would stand there back to back with another vampire, regaurdless if he had just saved her life, pointing a gun steadily at one target completely surrounded. Even though she did tremble slightly it is almost absurb to think that is her only reaction to the situation at hand. It is then that one from the mass steps out, answering Steven's question defiantly. </strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
