<br>
Her aim was impecable though, too bad this was the only gun she had. The bullent sent one down to the ground the bullet having gone straight through his skull, much to her surprize though the bullet exploded, igniting the vampire's head on fire. She would have never expected to find a gun like this on a vampire. Nevermind that now though she thought as she fire two more round, taking down two more, though they were all coming fast and as she clicked to fire she heard the terrifying click of an empty barrel. She literally cursed out loud this time, looking for an escape from the rush, but she was surrounded, completely. She had to have faith in this man now, he was her only hope.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkalaberia.showUserPublicProfile?gid=stevendeschain>Steven Deschain</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><i>~Kalaberia Citizen~</i></span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#8B4513>(8/8/03 1:11 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Intervension of Fate?</span><hr size=1> Steven quickly spins infront of her, pulling the desert eagle from under his jacket and placing it into her hand.  As he growls loudly he reaches under the back of his jacket, pulling a rather large blade from underneath the leather.  He smiles as he holds it in both hands, quickly deciding which of the foes to take on first.<br>
<br>
Three of the young vampires dive at him.  He reacts quickly, becoming a blue of blue from his shirt and hair, the blade slicing through the air and straight through the necks of the tree vampires, their heads flying from the quickly.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Fourteen more,</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> Steven thought to himself.  He pulls out a second gun from under her jacket and unleashes a few rounds straight into the skulls of four more of the other vampires.  A few of these younglings his loudly and scatter.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>6 more.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkalaberia.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vaniadelarian>Vania Delarian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><i>~Kalaberia Citizen~</i></span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#8B4513>(8/8/03 1:20 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://image1ex.villagephotos.com/1898960.jpg width=125 height=200></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Intervension of Fate?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Vania looked at the gun for only a moment, she had never fired a desert eagle before, but she figured it had to be simple enough. She took aim quickly, a true marksman, the first shot missed her target, not expecting the back fire to be so bad but she quickly recovered and fired four more times, knocking down all four of her targets, before whirling around landing on her knee's fireing right under Steven's arm her aim perfect as she landed a shot directly in the middle of another vampire's face, blowing him back hard. The last vampire merely ran in fear after relizing he was the last. Vania stood slowly, offering the gun back to the man whose name she still did not know. Her voice was soft, but not fearful. </strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
